        <body><div type="bibliography">
                
                <p><bibl><ptr target="#oliverio1916"/>, pp. 185-186, n. <citedRange>5</citedRange></bibl>, whence 
                    <bibl><ptr target="#SEG"/>, <citedRange>9.178</citedRange></bibl>;
                    <bibl><ptr target="#IGCyr"/> <citedRange>023500</citedRange></bibl>.
                    Cf. <bibl><ptr target="#cdl2016"/>, pp. <citedRange>252-253</citedRange>, whence
                        <bibl><ptr target="#SEG"/>, <citedRange>66.2318</citedRange></bibl>.</bibl>
                </p>
            </div><div type="edition" xml:lang="grc" xml:space="preserve">
                
                <ab>
                    <lb n="1"/><persName type="attested"><name nymRef="#_αρχος"><seg part="F"><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>αρχος</seg></name>
                        <persName type="attested" key="http://clas-lgpn2.classics.ox.ac.uk/cgi-bin/lgpn_search.cgi?id=V1-65473"><name type="patronymic" nymRef="#Πρατομήδης">Πρατομήδε<supplied reason="lost">υς</supplied></name></persName></persName>,
                    <lb n="2"/><persName type="attested"><name nymRef="#_στράτων"><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/><seg part="F"><supplied reason="lost">στ</supplied>ράτων</seg></name>
                        <persName type="attested" key="http://clas-lgpn2.classics.ox.ac.uk/cgi-bin/lgpn_search.cgi?id=V1-63218"><name type="patronymic" nymRef="#Ἀρίστων">Ἀρίστω<supplied reason="lost">νος</supplied></name></persName></persName>,
                    <lb n="3"/><persName type="attested"><name nymRef="#_ξίμαχος"><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/><seg part="F">ξίμαχος</seg></name> 
                        <persName type="attested" key="http://clas-lgpn2.classics.ox.ac.uk/cgi-bin/lgpn_search.cgi?id=V1-63778"><name type="patronymic" nymRef="#Εὐαγόρας">Εὐαγό<supplied reason="lost">ρα</supplied></name></persName></persName>,
                    <lb n="4"/><persName type="attested" key="http://clas-lgpn2.classics.ox.ac.uk/cgi-bin/lgpn_search.cgi?id=V1-64532"><name nymRef="#Καλλιφύης"><supplied reason="lost">Καλλι</supplied>φύης</name> 
                        <persName type="attested" key="http://clas-lgpn2.classics.ox.ac.uk/cgi-bin/lgpn_search.cgi?id=V1-64087"><name type="patronymic" nymRef="#Θάρσων">Θάρσων<supplied reason="lost">ος</supplied></name></persName></persName>,
                    <lb n="5"/><gap reason="lost" quantity="1" unit="line"/>

	 </ab>
            </div><div type="apparatus" xml:space="preserve">
            
                <p>
                    <app loc="4">
                        <lem><supplied reason="lost">Καλλι</supplied>φύης</lem>
                        <rdg resp="#oliverio1916"><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>φύης</rdg>
                    </app>
                </p>
 </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="fr" xml:space="preserve">
            <p> <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>arkhos fils de Pratomèdès, <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>stratôn fils d'Aristôn, <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>ximakhos fils d'Euagoras, Kalliphuès fils de Tharsôn, <gap reason="lost" quantity="1" unit="line"/></p>
         </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="en" xml:space="preserve">
            <p> <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>archos son of Pratomedes, <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>straton son of Ariston, <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>ximachos son of Euagoras, Kalliphues son of Tharson, <gap reason="lost" quantity="1" unit="line"/></p>
         </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="it" xml:space="preserve">
            <p> <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>archos figlio di Pratomedes, <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>straton figlio di Ariston, <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>ximachos figlio di Euagoras, Kalliphues figlio di Tharson, <gap reason="lost" quantity="1" unit="line"/></p>
         </div><div type="commentary">
                
                <p>For the date, Oliverio said «<foreign xml:lang="it">buona epoca</foreign>»; <bibl><ptr target="#SEG"/>, <citedRange>9.178</citedRange></bibl> has erroneously «second century BC». C. Dobias-Lalou says from photograph 'third century BC'.</p>
                <p>With such a date, compounds in <foreign xml:lang="grc">-φύης</foreign> are very few in Cyrenaica; the father's name being the same, the name at l. 4 may be taken as 
                  identical with that at <ref type="inscription" source="#IGCyr2">IGCyr065210</ref>, l. 97.</p>
	<p>The lettering being homongeneous, this should not be a list of priests, as suggested by Hondius in <bibl><ptr target="#SEG"/></bibl>, whereas Oliverio cautiously mentioned a «<foreign xml:lang="it">lista pubblica</foreign>».</p>
            </div></body>
    </text>
